data.name: Roasted Pumpkin Seeds
data.quickTastyDescription: Crispy, flavorful roasted pumpkin seeds, perfect for snacking!
detailedCookingInstructions: If the pumpkin seeds are not already cleaned, rinse them in cold water to remove the pumpkin flesh and strings, then pat them dry with a towel.
In a bowl, combine the pumpkin seeds, olive oil, salt, garlic powder, and paprika. Toss well to coat the seeds evenly.
Spread the seasoned seeds in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Roast in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes, stirring halfway through, until they are golden brown and crispy.
Remove from the oven, let cool, and enjoy!
